<h2>Reference</h2>

<p>For what it's worth, in Wikipedia there's a proposal to merge <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hackintosh" rel="nofollow noreferrer">hackintosh</a> into <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OSx86" rel="nofollow noreferrer">OSx86</a>. </p>

<p>Of the two pages, the page for OSx86 is vastly more fleshy, and (like <a href="https://apple.meta.stackexchange.com/q/2/8546">Can one ask Hackintosh questions on Ask Different?</a>) includes coverage of legal issues and Apple objections. In Ask Different tag info for OSx86, we could simply refer to the Wikipedia page, and so help to avoid excessive chat in Stack Exchange. So of the two tags, my preference would be <strong>osx86</strong>.</p>


